subject: Google Cloud Career Launchpad Student Interest Form
text: Google Forms      Thanks for filling in Google Cloud Career Launchpad Student Interest Form  Here's what was received.    Edit response      Google Cloud Career Launchpad Student Interest Form    Thank you for your interest in the Google Cloud Career Launchpad    (previously Career Readiness) program. We have so much in store for you and    can't wait to have you onboard. üí™    What will you learn with the Google Cloud Career Launchpad program?  The Career Launchpad program is our effort to help students start a career    in the field of cloud and eventually get started with their first job or    internship. The program is ideal for students aspiring to launch careers in    engineering and management roles related to cloud infrastructure,    cloud-native application development, and data engineering.    Do I have to pay anything for the program?      Not at all! The learning content of the program is completely FREE OF COST    and Google will bear its cost for you.  On top of the learning content, we also provide 50% discount to students on    the OPTIONAl Google Cloud certifications which students can take if they    are interested otherwise can skip.    Get a chance to be shortlisted for Google Cloud Career Fair (India    ONLY) üë©‚Äçüíºüë®‚Äçüíº  And how can we forget - as part of the Career Launchpad program, you will    also get a chance to get shortlisted for the Google Cloud Career Fair that    we organise every year where we will help you get connected with potential    employers for a face-to-face interview opportunity towards your first job    or internship. üèÜ  (See below)      Email *      soham.k1804@gmail.com      Confirm your Email Address *    Please make sure that there are NO typos or errors in your email otherwise    you will not receive the email invitation to the program      soham.k1804@gmail.com      Google Cloud Career Fair (India ONLY)      Captionless Image      Terms & Conditions    ******  TERMS AND CONDITIONS    Google reserves the right to determine Your eligibility for the Google    Cloud Career Launchpad program.    By submitting this form, You, on behalf of yourself and the organization    you represent, if applicable, ('You') agree to these terms and conditions:    The credit is valid for Google Cloud training and certification and is    subject to Your acceptance of the applicable terms of service for the    training and certification platforms. The credit is non-transferable and    may not be sold or bartered. Unused credit expires on the date indicated on    the media conveying the credit information. The credit may be issued in    increments as You use the credit over the period of time during which the    credit is valid. Offer void where prohibited by law. The credits do not    have commercial value and may not be used for commercial purposes. Google    reserves the right to determine an individual's eligibility for training    and certification credits.    If You are a student, You represent that the credit can only be used in    Your capacity as a student of Your educational institution for skill    building and career development purposes and not for Your personal or hobby    use.    In addition, Credits may not be used to engage in mining cryptocurrency    unless You obtain Google's written consent in advance, which consent may be    revoked by Google in its discretion at any time.    You represent that (i) the credit is consistent with all applicable laws    and regulations, including relevant ethics rules and laws; (ii) the    provision of credits will not negatively impact Google's current or future    ability to do business with your educational institution, (iii) You are not    a resident of a US embargoed country, (v) You are not ordinarily a resident    in a US embargoed country, and (iv) You are not otherwise prohibited by    applicable export controls and sanctions programs from participating in the    credit redemption program.    Communication & Tracking  * Google may contact you via email to provision benefits and send surveys    and other communication related to the Google Cloud Career Launchpad    program.  * By joining, you agree to Google Cloud Training & the faculty members of    your institution tracking your grades and other activity in the learning    program.  * By joining, you agree to share your contact information with the faculty    members of your institution so that they can reach out to you and help    during the learning program.      I have read the above terms *      Yes, I accept the terms      I decline (By declining, you will not receive the invitation for the    program)      Fill out your details    We are so happy that you have made it here and are interested in taking    part in the Google Cloud Career Launchpad program. Please take a minute and    fill out your details below so that we can onboard you to the program and    send you enrolment instructions      Your full name *      Soham Chetan Kulkarni      Your contact number    We collect this information to share this with potential employers in the    future when you graduate.  Note: This is an OPTIONAL field, if you do not wish to share your contact    number, please leave it blank.      8805814877      Gender *      Male        Select your institution from the list below *      Shri Vithal Education & Research Institute        If selected 'Others' above, then specify your institution name      Select your current academic year *      First Year      Second Year      Third Year      Fourth Year      Fifth Year & above      Graduated      In which year are you graduating/graduated? *    For Example: 2023, 2024, 2025, etc.      2026      Do you have access to a working internet connection and a laptop with    latest chrome browser? *    Note: This is a minimum requirement for you to participate in the program.      Yes      No      Do you have an account on Google Cloud Skills Boost -    https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/? *      Yes, I already have an account      No, i want to create one      Submit your Google Cloud Skills Boost Profile URL    Great! You have a Google Cloud Skills Boost account. Please do remember to    share your profile below so that we can track your progress in the program    and send you your prizes when you win      Log-in to https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/ if not already logged in  Once logged-in, then go to https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/profile/.  Now click on the red underlined button 'Make profile public' below your    account picture and then click 'Make Profile Public' if there's a pop-up.    (See screenshot below)  Give some time for the page to load. Once it loads, you will be on your    profile page. Now just share the URL displayed there. (That's your profile    URL)  Here is a small video (just 1 minute) that will walk you through how to do    this and get your profile URL - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C7Zb3cqEkwA  (You can watch it at 2x speed to go faster)        (If the above video doesn't work for you, then refer to this video instead    - https://youtu.be/uFvfMngxYXQ?si=gU2cB3roVVbv_l3l)      Get your GCSB Public Profile URL    Captionless Image      [VERY IMPORTANT] Please share your Google Cloud Skills Boost Public Profile    URL (See how to get your profile URL-    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C7Zb3cqEkwA) *    Here's what it should look like -    https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/public_profiles/PROFILE_ID  (DO NOT copy-paste this as your application will be REJECTED)      https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/public_profiles/d6aaf7ba-cca8-41e3-995c-b1f7035193df      I understand that if I submitted a wrong profile URL above then I will NOT    receive the invitation to the program *      ‚úì  I understand      Select your track for the program    We have 5 different tracks in the program that your faculty member(s) have    chosen from. Based on what your faculty has chosen, you need to select the    same track below so that you can be assigned to their group on Google Cloud    Skills boost and receive the invitation for the program.        Note:        It might be possible that they are multiple faculty members in your    institution and they have chosen either 1 or 2 or all the 5 tracks. So    before selecting your own track below, please reach out to your faculty and    confirm the track(s) they have opted for and then make your selection. If    you already know this, then please go ahead and select the track.  Also, each student can choose only 1 track. We have provided some    information below for all the 5 tracks. Please read the same VERY CAREFULLY    before you make the selection. Once invited, you will NOT be allowed to    change your track.      For more information, please feel free to reach out to your faculty    directly.      See information about all the 6 tracks below    Here are the available tracks in the program and some information about    them that would help you make a decision of which one to select:        Cloud Engineering Certificate (ACE)  You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students who have little to no experience    with cloud computing and want to start from scratch.  See the content and curriculum for the ACE track here. It consists of ~80    hours of content with 6 on-demand courses and 4 lab-based courses (skill    badges).  [Optional Offering] Associate Cloud Engineer exam is also part of this    track as OPTIONAL. Students who successfully complete the training get a    50% discount and faculty members get a 100% discount on the 1st attempt of    the exam.  Cloud Digital Leader Course Series (CDL)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students with business backgrounds like    MBA and wants to understand the business aspects of cloud  See the content and curriculum for the CDL track here. It consists of ~9    hours of content with 6 on-demand courses.  [Optional Offering] Cloud Digital Leader exam is also part of this track as    OPTIONAL. Students who successfully complete the training get a 50%    discount and faculty members get a 100% discount on the 1st attempt of the    exam.  Data Analytics Certificate (ADP)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students who have keen interest in data    analysis.  See the content and curriculum for the DA track here. It consists of ~90    hours of content with 4 on-demand courses + 1 Capstone project at the end +    1 preparatory course for Associate Data Practitioner exam.  [Optional Offering] Associate Data Practitioner exam is also part of this    track as OPTIONAL. Students who successfully complete the training get a    50% discount and faculty members get a 100% discount on the 1st attempt of    the exam.  Cloud Cybersecurity Certificate (CYBER)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students who have keen interest in cloud    based security and helps prepare learners for roles like Developer Security    Operations.  See the content and curriculum for the CYBER track here. It consists of ~90    hours of content with 4 on-demand courses + 1 Capstone project at the end.  No global level certification offered in this track yet.  Generative AI Course Series (GAIL)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This 2 course pathway series helps learners build expertise in generative    AI and its fundamentals ranging from large language models, responsible AI    and Gemini as well.  See the content and curriculum for all 2 pathways of the AI track here &    here. It consists of ~30 hours of content with 2 on-demand courses    consisting of 1 skill badge credential.  No global level certification offered in this track yet.    Google Cloud Computing Foundations (GCCF)      You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This certificate program provides individuals with little to no background    or experience in cloud computing a detailed overview of concepts covering    cloud basics, big data, machine learning, and where and how Google Cloud    fits in.  See the content and curriculum for the GCCF track here. It consists of ~40    hours of content with 4 on-demand courses + 4 lab-based courses.  No global level certification offered in this track yet.        Select your track for the program *    Please make sure to read the information above for each track before moving    forward.      Cloud Engineering Certificate (ACE)      Cloud Digital Leader Course Series (CDL)      Data Analytics Certificate (ADP)      Cloud Cybersecurity Certificate (CYBER)      Generative AI Course Series (GAIL)      Google Cloud Computing Foundations (GCCF)      I acknowledge that if I selected a track that is not opted by my faculty    members, then I would be by default assigned to the ACE track or the track    they have opted for if its not the ACE track. *      I acknowledge      [README] What should you expect after you submit the form?    Once you submit the form, we will check:      Whether you have submitted the right profile URL or not. If not, then you    will have to go back and fill the form again otherwise you will not receive    the program invitation.  Whether the deadline for your institution has passed or not. Only those    submissions will be counted which were made during the institution deadline.  Once the above conditions are met, we will confirm your participation from    your faculty and will send you the program invitation.    In case of any queries, do remember to reach out to your faculty member.      Create your own Google Form    Does this form look suspicious? Report

subject: Funds/Securities Balance
text:
Dear Investor,

With reference to NSE circulars NSE/INSP/46704 dated December 17, 2020, and NSE/INSP/55039 dated December 28, 2022, Trading members are required to upload clients' securities balance on a daily basis.

Further, with reference to NCL circular NCL/CMPL/49348 dated Aug 20, 2021, and NSE circular NSE/INSP/49691 dated September 22, 2021, Members are required to upload disaggregated collateral information (segment-wise and asset type wise) at the client level to their Clearing corporations on a daily basis.

Information pertaining to your fund and securities balance as on {{last_date_of_saturday}} provided by {{tm_name}} along with the details of securities ISIN wise is attached.

Please follow the procedure given below for opening the attachment:

  1. Click on the attachment provided with this mail.
  2. You will be prompted for your password.
  3. The password is your PAN number in upper case.

Please note that negative number in the file represents debit balance/balance payable by you. Also, the funds and securities balances provided are what is maintained with your broker and does not include balance in your personal bank account and demat account.

You are advised to compare the funds, securities and commodities balances received from Exchange on a weekly basis with the balances in the weekly statement of accounts for funds, securities and commodities sent by the stockbroker for the respective date. In case you find any discrepancy in the balances, we advise you to take up the matter immediately with your Broker.You may contact customer service at {{tm_email_id}} or {{tm_contact_no}}.

In case of non-resolution of discrepancy by the broker, you may intimate the same to the Exchange at ignse@nse.co.in or 18002660050 or register an online complaint at https://smartodr.in/login.

The data is being provided to the clients on an 'as is' and 'what-is' basis as provided by the trading member. The Exchange shall not be liable for any delays, errors, omissions, commissions, inaccuracies in rendering the data. In no event shall the Exchange be liable for any damages, including without limitation direct or indirect, special, incidental, or consequential damages, losses or expenses arising in connection with the data provided by the Exchange through this facility.

You are requested to note that in the event of trading member being declared as defaulter/expelled, all transactions executed on the exchange trading platform within 90 calendar days prior to the effective date of disablement of the trading member or after the latest monthly/quarterly settlement date, if any, in respect of the claimant whichever is later shall be considered eligible for compensation from IPFT subject to Rules, Byelaws, Regulations, guidelines etc. of the Exchange and SEBI circulars and subject to the appropriate norms laid down by the relevant Committee. For details, you may refer the policy hosted on the website https://static.nseindia.com//s3fs-public/inline-files/Policy_for_evaluation_of_claims_0.pdf

For Information & Education Purpose

We would like to draw your attention to 'SEBI vide circular dated April 04, 2022, wherein they have introduced the mechanism of ‚ÄúDemat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI)‚Äù. The DDPI shall serve the same purpose of POA and significantly mitigate the misuse of POA. You should be aware that the stockbroker and depository participant cannot directly / indirectly compel the clients to execute the DDPI or deny services to the client if the client refuses to execute the DDPI.

Please refer to SEBI Circular dated October 06, 2022, for the list of instructions which client can give to its stockbroker / depository participant. You may refer the following link for same: https://www.sebi.gov.in/legal/circulars/oct-2022/execution-of-demat-debit-and-pledge-instruction-ddpi-for-transfer-of-securities-towards-deliveries-settlement-obligations-and-pledging-re-pledging-of-securities-clarification_63724.html Should you wish to give any instructions, these need to be signed in physical against each purpose of DDPI. In case of an eSign option is made available, client should be given an option to choose the specific purpose(s) of DDPI'.

Dos and Don‚Äôts for Retail Investors:
  1. Please deal with SEBI registered intermediaries only. Ensure that you have complete knowledge of the products and the risks involved before investing.
  2. Offering fixed/guaranteed/regular returns/ capital protection schemes in stock markets whether written or oral is not allowed. Brokers or any of their representatives or Authorised Persons cannot enter into any loan agreement to pay interest on the funds/securities offered by you.
  3. Do not fall prey to emails, SMSs and online videos luring you to trade in stock/ securities / schemes promising high returns/profits.
  4. Ensure to fill all the required details in the 'KYC' document by yourself and receive duly signed copy of your 'KYC' documents from your broker.
  5. Trading in derivatives involves high risk and accordingly investors should understand the product well before trading in such segments/products.
  6. Opt for electronic (e-mail) contract notes/financial statements only if you are computer savvy and have your own e-mail account.
  7. Do not share your login ID, password, OTP, TPIN with any person including employees of the broker or Authorised Person under any circumstances.
  8. Ensure that all your trades are executed as per your instructions.
  9. Insure you receive the payout of funds and securities within 1 working day of settlement. In case you have chosen running account of funds, ensure your account is settled on first Friday/Saturday of every month / quarter as opted for.
  10. Dealing in cash is prohibited. Do not place any securities with the broker or associate of the broker or authorized person of the broker. Do not transfer securities as margin/ collateral to the broker and such securities only must be pledged from the client demat account.
  11. Opt for Demat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI) only for transfer of securities for deliveries/settlement obligations, initiating pledging of securities for margins, and for mutual fund/open offer transactions on Exchange platform. DDPI/PoA are optional and should not be insisted on for opening the account.
  12. Always keep your mobile number and email id updated with your broker. Don't ignore any SMSs / e-mails with regards to contract notes/trades/funds and securities balances sent by broker/Exchange. Verify the details of the same and report discrepancy, if any, to your broker in writing immediately.
  13. Please verify the bank account details of the broker from the website of broker/Exchange before transferring funds to the broker.
  14. Claims for funds or securities given to the broker under any arrangement/ agreement of indicative return or claims for funds, without transactions on the Exchange will not be accepted by the Exchange in case of default by your broker.
  15. For more details on Investor awareness, please visit-www.nseindia.com/invest/investors-home
  16. For more information related to investments in securities market, please visit SEBI Investor Website - https://investor.sebi.gov.in and SEBI Saa‚Çπthi Mobile App.

www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-know-your-rights

You may also visit our website www.nseindia.com for any further information that you may require or email your queries to the email ID ignse@nse.co.in, quoting the name of your city in the subject. We would be glad to assist you.

Information to investors:

Exchange has introduced trading in Rights Entitlement w.e.f. May 20, 2020. The trades executed, if any, for Rights Entitlement in Capital Market shall form part of the attached file. Rights Entitlement should not be mistaken for ordinary shares and unless Rights Entitlement are exercised they will lose value and no rights (shares) will be available to the investor. The buyer of the Rights Entitlement is required to subscribe for the same before the Issue Closing Date, else the same will lapse and no shares will be allotted.

In case you need any clarification, please feel free to call on our toll-free number 1800 266 0050 (select option 5 - UCI & Trade Alerts). You can also email us at uci@nse.co.in, quoting your PAN, Mobile no. and your query.

To learn more about Personal Finance, securities market, details of upcoming Investor Awareness Programs and more, please visit the SEBI Investor website at https://investor.sebi.gov.in

Thanks and Regards,

text: YouTube Gaming    <https://c.gle/ANiao5plaqIXGrMSR2DqFEr0ktMwaF_PjBlW-e1lJamjnIy-FvPQ2pOMgu5JCgYk1uFTszvNtZSsMIaeulGLUA5jH8NB9-BoZ2k6akvANovaLSjSaNH28Q5jZSF594O2EDVK91JF4AWJkA>      Learn how to improve your Tony Hawk's Pro Skater game with tips from    YouTube Creator andyTHPS.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5o0718If3XM9Bv4_oW3onxLZaJ8WTpV_2Vc-geQrqRhcNw_zLuGhQfid_N9Vb6lyBiBCu3I6B8Sny0XrxZaVFF4hffMa-VKK3HpcSUcFh_IYOtd1Nl-UlvKPR8E10WJlGbjqqqLKO6jv-FxNjAd1_WhwcnolPB0rK6e8kwfl1w>  10 tips to improve your skills for Tony Hawk's Pro Skater      Ready for the release of Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 3 + 4? subject: Funds/Securities Balance
text:
Dear Investor,

With reference to NSE circulars NSE/INSP/46704 dated December 17, 2020, and NSE/INSP/55039 dated December 28, 2022, Trading members are required to upload clients' securities balance on a daily basis.

Further, with reference to NCL circular NCL/CMPL/49348 dated Aug 20, 2021, and NSE circular NSE/INSP/49691 dated September 22, 2021, Members are required to upload disaggregated collateral information (segment-wise and asset type wise) at the client level to their Clearing corporations on a daily basis.

Information pertaining to your fund and securities balance as on {{last_date_of_saturday}} provided by {{tm_name}} along with the details of securities ISIN wise is attached.

Please follow the procedure given below for opening the attachment:

  1. Click on the attachment provided with this mail.
  2. You will be prompted for your password.
  3. The password is your PAN number in upper case.

Please note that negative number in the file represents debit balance/balance payable by you. Also, the funds and securities balances provided are what is maintained with your broker and does not include balance in your personal bank account and demat account.

You are advised to compare the funds, securities and commodities balances received from Exchange on a weekly basis with the balances in the weekly statement of accounts for funds, securities and commodities sent by the stockbroker for the respective date. In case you find any discrepancy in the balances, we advise you to take up the matter immediately with your Broker.You may contact customer service at {{tm_email_id}} or {{tm_contact_no}}.

In case of non-resolution of discrepancy by the broker, you may intimate the same to the Exchange at ignse@nse.co.in or 18002660050 or register an online complaint at https://smartodr.in/login.

The data is being provided to the clients on an 'as is' and 'what-is' basis as provided by the trading member. The Exchange shall not be liable for any delays, errors, omissions, commissions, inaccuracies in rendering the data. In no event shall the Exchange be liable for any damages, including without limitation direct or indirect, special, incidental, or consequential damages, losses or expenses arising in connection with the data provided by the Exchange through this facility.

You are requested to note that in the event of trading member being declared as defaulter/expelled, all transactions executed on the exchange trading platform within 90 calendar days prior to the effective date of disablement of the trading member or after the latest monthly/quarterly settlement date, if any, in respect of the claimant whichever is later shall be considered eligible for compensation from IPFT subject to Rules, Byelaws, Regulations, guidelines etc. of the Exchange and SEBI circulars and subject to the appropriate norms laid down by the relevant Committee. For details, you may refer the policy hosted on the website https://static.nseindia.com//s3fs-public/inline-files/Policy_for_evaluation_of_claims_0.pdf

For Information & Education Purpose

We would like to draw your attention to 'SEBI vide circular dated April 04, 2022, wherein they have introduced the mechanism of ‚ÄúDemat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI)‚Äù. The DDPI shall serve the same purpose of POA and significantly mitigate the misuse of POA. You should be aware that the stockbroker and depository participant cannot directly / indirectly compel the clients to execute the DDPI or deny services to the client if the client refuses to execute the DDPI.

Please refer to SEBI Circular dated October 06, 2022, for the list of instructions which client can give to its stockbroker / depository participant. You may refer the following link for same: https://www.sebi.gov.in/legal/circulars/oct-2022/execution-of-demat-debit-and-pledge-instruction-ddpi-for-transfer-of-securities-towards-deliveries-settlement-obligations-and-pledging-re-pledging-of-securities-clarification_63724.html Should you wish to give any instructions, these need to be signed in physical against each purpose of DDPI. In case of an eSign option is made available, client should be given an option to choose the specific purpose(s) of DDPI'.

Dos and Don‚Äôts for Retail Investors:
  1. Please deal with SEBI registered intermediaries only. Ensure that you have complete knowledge of the products and the risks involved before investing.
  2. Offering fixed/guaranteed/regular returns/ capital protection schemes in stock markets whether written or oral is not allowed. Brokers or any of their representatives or Authorised Persons cannot enter into any loan agreement to pay interest on the funds/securities offered by you.
  3. Do not fall prey to emails, SMSs and online videos luring you to trade in stock/ securities / schemes promising high returns/profits.
  4. Ensure to fill all the required details in the 'KYC' document by yourself and receive duly signed copy of your 'KYC' documents from your broker.
  5. Trading in derivatives involves high risk and accordingly investors should understand the product well before trading in such segments/products.
  6. Opt for electronic (e-mail) contract notes/financial statements only if you are computer savvy and have your own e-mail account.
  7. Do not share your login ID, password, OTP, TPIN with any person including employees of the broker or Authorised Person under any circumstances.
  8. Ensure that all your trades are executed as per your instructions.
  9. Insure you receive the payout of funds and securities within 1 working day of settlement. In case you have chosen running account of funds, ensure your account is settled on first Friday/Saturday of every month / quarter as opted for.
  10. Dealing in cash is prohibited. Do not place any securities with the broker or associate of the broker or authorized person of the broker. Do not transfer securities as margin/ collateral to the broker and such securities only must be pledged from the client demat account.
  11. Opt for Demat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI) only for transfer of securities for deliveries/settlement obligations, initiating pledging of securities for margins, and for mutual fund/open offer transactions on Exchange platform. DDPI/PoA are optional and should not be insisted on for opening the account.
  12. Always keep your mobile number and email id updated with your broker. Don't ignore any SMSs / e-mails with regards to contract notes/trades/funds and securities balances sent by broker/Exchange. Verify the details of the same and report discrepancy, if any, to your broker in writing immediately.
  13. Please verify the bank account details of the broker from the website of broker/Exchange before transferring funds to the broker.
  14. Claims for funds or securities given to the broker under any arrangement/ agreement of indicative return or claims for funds, without transactions on the Exchange will not be accepted by the Exchange in case of default by your broker.
  15. For more details on Investor awareness, please visit-www.nseindia.com/invest/investors-home
  16. For more information related to investments in securities market, please visit SEBI Investor Website - https://investor.sebi.gov.in and SEBI Saa‚Çπthi Mobile App.

We are glad to inform you that NSE for your convenience/comfort is providing links below on investment concepts, investor alerts, your rights and obligation as an investor.

www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-know-your-rights
www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-fraud-dos-and-donts
www.nseindia.com/invest/file-a-complaint-online

You may also visit our website www.nseindia.com for any further information that you may require or email your queries to the email ID ignse@nse.co.in, quoting the name of your city in the subject. We would be glad to assist you.

Information to investors:

Exchange has introduced trading in Rights Entitlement w.e.f. May 20, 2020. The trades executed, if any, for Rights Entitlement in Capital Market shall form part of the attached file. Rights Entitlement should not be mistaken for ordinary shares and unless Rights Entitlement are exercised they will lose value and no rights (shares) will be available to the investor. The buyer of the Rights Entitlement is required to subscribe for the same before the Issue Closing Date, else the same will lapse and no shares will be allotted.

In case you need any clarification, please feel free to call on our toll-free number 1800 266 0050 (select option 5 - UCI & Trade Alerts). You can also email us at uci@nse.co.in, quoting your PAN, Mobile no. and your query.

To learn more about Personal Finance, securities market, details of upcoming Investor Awareness Programs and more, please visit the SEBI Investor website at https://investor.sebi.gov.in

Thanks and Regards,
National Stock Exchange of India Limited

text: https://flutterflow.io/      ** üå≥ Branching Improvements  ------------------------------------------------------------    We know branching can be tricky‚Äîespecially for big projects with lots of contributors. We‚Äôre actively working to make it faster and smoother.    While there‚Äôs still more to do (performance is a key focus), here are some recent improvements:  * Better Navigation: Filter by category in the merge sidebar and use advanced search (Match Case, Match Whole Word, or top-level only).  * Smarter Merging: We‚Äôve improved merge speed, especially for projects with lots of translations. We also use Git to better detect unchanged files.  * Less Stale Branches: You‚Äôll now see a stale branch dialog when trying to merge a branch that‚Äôs been hanging around for longer than a week.  * Safer Conflict Resolution: When resolving a conflict, you can now Copy Nested Files, which helps keep your components intact and prevents broken dependencies.  * Heads Up: We removed the option to duplicate a project with branches since that flow led to unexpected behavior for some users.        ** ‚úÖ Bulk User Management  ------------------------------------------------------------    You can now bulk invite team members to a project and update their roles all at once‚Äîno more one-by-one clicks.    Paste a list of emails (comma-separated or line-separated), and FlutterFlow will automatically detect and format them for you to make it easy to invite them.    Use checkboxes to select multiple users and adjust their access levels in bulk. If the selected users have different access levels, we‚Äôll show the options that are available to everyone (for example, you can remove access from all selected users or downgrade them to Read-only if that‚Äôs valid).    This works with search, filters, and sorting too‚Äîso you can easily find just the group you want to update.        ** ‚ôø Focus Borders  ------------------------------------------------------------    We‚Äôve added focus borders to make your apps easier to navigate with keyboards or assistive technologies.    How to use it:  * Add an action to a widget  * Go to the widget‚Äôs Accessibility options  * Toggle Show Border on Focus  * Customize the Border Width, Color, and Radius to match your design      ** üõ†Ô∏è Other Improvements  ------------------------------------------------------------  * Wait (Delay) action now accepts variable duration.  * Added /listPartitionedFileFields endpoint to Project API to list all possible fields (not nested) for a given filename.  * Updated AI Agent models to stable versions of Gemini 2.5 Pro and Flash.  * Disabled WASM in Test Mode to improve reload performance.  * Enhanced text scaling to automatically respect device accessibility settings when app-level scaling is at default, while maintaining priority for explicit in-app text scaling controls.      **  üêû Bug Fixes  ------------------------------------------------------------  * Fixed an issue where Test Mode would not display error messages on build failures.  * Fixed iOS Local Run issues with Firebase App Check enforcement by enabling iOS App Check debug tokens.  * Fixed an issue when deploying CORS proxy functions via Firebase.  * Fixed an issue where loops within action callback parameters did not function correctly.  * Fixed an issue where accessing parent loop values from a nested loop failed.  * Fixed an issue where Loop over List operations failed in Action Blocks.  * Fixed JSON path operations incorrectly converting Map objects to strings, which was causing crashes when trying to parse nested JSON data into custom data types.  * Fixed an issue that blocked renaming of DataTables.  * Fixed an issue where library page routes would not be updated correctly if the route was never overridden.  * Fixed an issue with Supabase streaming where query results were not accessible in On Data Change actions.  * Fixed the visibility of the 'Generate with AI' button in the page selection panel.  * Fixed an issue where the first element of a RichText could not be edited.  * Fixed an issue where projects would be updated even if custom files hadn‚Äôt changed.  * Fixed an issue with playing asset audio on Android.  * Fixed an issue with build.gradle not consistently updating when unlocked.  * Fixed an issue where invalid variables could be inappropriately set.  * Fixed an issue where package.json could not be edited in the Cloud Functions tab.  * Fixed an issue where AppDelegate.swift changes would not reflect in exported code.      ** üöÄ ICYMI: DreamFlow  ------------------------------------------------------------    The next evolution of DreamFlow is here and available at www.dreamflow.app (http://www.dreamflow.app/) . DreamFlow now gives you the power to edit visually, write code, or let the agent handle changes for you. You‚Äôll see a sharper experience that lets you:    ‚Ä¢ Start with a prompt to break the blank page  ‚Ä¢ Build visually with intuitive controls  ‚Ä¢ Refine with precision in real code    This is tri-surface development - agentic, visual, and code - built for speed, flexibility, and full control. Watch Dreamflow in action (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yN15o1F8dic) .      ** üèóÔ∏è New Features We're Working On  ------------------------------------------------------------  * An AI chatbot that uses context from our internal Technical Support Team to provide answers to you instantly.  * MCP support  * Building some exciting product updates for FFDC 2025 (https://www.ffdc.io/) !    Have a Technical Question or Issue?  If you need help building in FlutterFlow, you can sign up for office hours with one of our Developer Relations Team members here (https://calendly.com/d/ck9k-hzz-ywc/flutterflow-devrel-office-hours?month=2024-10) .    ============================================================  ** FlutterFlow Logo (https://flutterflow.io)    Build Different.    You are receiving this email because you signed up on ** flutterflow.io (https://flutterflow.io)  ** YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC5LueiosDVInA6yXE_38i9Q)  ** Twitter (http://www.twitter.com/flutterflow)  ** LinkedIn (https://www.linkedin.com/company/flutterflow)  ** Website (https://www.flutterflow.io)  ¬© 2025 FlutterFlow, Inc.    Our mailing address:  883 N Shoreline Blvd, #B220,  Mountain View, CA 94043    Want to change how you receive these emails?  You can ** update your preferences (https://flutterflow.us2.list-manage.com/profile?u=544d5264f5e71e5fa379d41f5&id=43c1c0eebb&e=0a9d458d40&c=f672fbbfcc)  or ** unsubscribe from this list (https://flutterflow.us2.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=544d5264f5e71e5fa379d41f5&id=43c1c0eebb&t=b&e=0a9d458d40&c=f672fbbfcc)  .

subject: =?UTF-8?Q?The_overwhelmed_person=E2=80=99s_guide_to_Google_Cloud=3A_Ju?=  	=?UTF-8?Q?ly_22?=
text: The overwhelmed person‚Äôs guide to Google Cloud By Richard Seroter    <mailto:rseroter@google.com>    New and shiny    Your agents got an upgrade with the new Vertex AI Agent Engine Memory Bank.    Our interactions with agents may span sessions and extend for some time.    You‚Äôve had to solve this with your own state solutions. But with the new    Memory Bank, you get a managed service that ‚Äújust works‚Äù for agents running    in Vertex AI Agent Engine. See the blog post    <https://c.gle/ANiao5o0sWOF9wVgO7HNzhO0XqPUcrk1gFCiZa1lgCUCSO0BDgxwJm6_12gADn4OTJj1_U7YMWWLSl95VqN4QeZr_Q6RFe7bwlchvpgOP6HxK5FC9BWJJNB4j2lVEWFCdPiRgcvoOF8cIhpa6BaqaWYySZI_zAiuC_M318aKeYj8JtOBNq5yHLIH2GjzH1cGkN5whywmiKj486bbXL_WSlTNBO1BkgJ9lNMuAoIW6UqYiFGwP3Jp>    and docs    <https://c.gle/ANiao5pFGBFD-KEHWDR6WDVFPcW2TFA4_EUb3TnN_XQcdd0uFwCXMEbSFADP9rGagE_YvPephDiqSFaTZZCl957XV9cxg0NhZJvPRaoLWhMnpa1XLt3OfvhvMfogN8mAm8BiFDM5v5oe6eLoIGmRHjEMS3Ja6JWKqgmNCA0u5tIQZwqA1V0yxQZcJI5d2wB4QRjIV5n1Doyr6VKtOA-6Bz-Zdzi3UaVu>    for more.    BigQuery gets some powerful new aggregation functions.    This won‚Äôt appeal to all of you, but to those dealing with rich data sets,    this might be a BIG deal. These three new categories of aggregation    functions    <https://c.gle/ANiao5pl2STjtSRbavUedgpGaWjaOZ3f2K3o0YF_5xrIjcUNECZWV3KAEIGc8kJT_i506eAbxiPPMUSGd00g-XZjJIHFAoGQ53J0D60O2VTf-ryNjCKsnaXdHNtMhcQKxFPRJ5ae9UoU-qgOpTJg5hy2unz9AU-6D78zm9elyGWDMn-QLLIHMBy2HUjHy3PqpnCWHpK-JaU5ZZ2GmgTwMFrHrxfqHknEb4JRTvBDsVPgbxil_hNQLiFNeRXElVRH3ItGwMTqJehcfP2z5Lax1Tcj>‚Äîgroup    by extension, user-defined aggregation functions, and approximate aggregate    functions‚Äîmay introduce massive performance and efficiency improvements.    Cloud Run introduces worker pools and new Docker integrations.    How do you deploy a background task that continuously chomps on work? Now    you can run these in Cloud Run worker    pools.<https://c.gle/ANiao5o9H-3zuxG4hU2DH5L8erWG9SsfoFi1sddeejVXg0BO1pnmQlB1GuQCgIyNDwo8IeoTz2xmLnaT6qirETyOFug8_EllT-KlViCDOHb0Qb3lzry8WhMk_vvyUdkR8syPubVKRfBsxb7Qs7zONzMWBhfmvL4tlvg33DgyCEjefFl20aR7VDpyN48NY9kLVGAGzhI>    It‚Äôs great for processing data from Apache Kafka, and we also introduced a    new open source Cloud Run Kafka Autoscaler.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5qcqU2bh2Wa1TewB06osRAmhUbqteo8lt4xiceDIA7Bz_KaeIGDNlSumh8d4qBSdqZAL0ely_TadzfjlGevuGE_TAj_ACtIBjsJgqdFPNChlk7HlL_8bmaF0c-uGPjhbzQBZSDEQAaXeYUF5mKDOp_yPVR4XAnRb8y097dQy2AZzlt_iL-tKBN3bs2p1AMHdWhOLDJiSNKqSPfAQKT6oIt10ofXmsOp1qhan_VczQQcXZytfKtJQbNre5qk5Q>    We also shared new integrations that make it easier to deploy Docker    Compose definitions to Cloud    Run.<https://c.gle/ANiao5p530S1bwilAsm7eGmrob9f7Pu_nNMYTw3qppcRgh-9JPb5hqFUDi8rR1UuL8RKYjDywbpUgkTHOP3fmjwLxvujFZ457R97JcFKygSnFBon4ErQSWrBoLd70jWrFf8LIAfBHo4nFkFRXcl3xJhqlo9JmGiAWZJ1p_FpEPxDCtsU_Yi5dan9RYUlAgL6-s33u74QwoD7crY0EVWynK1NmCRwoJePAXizL2QYO0iH20TrNt48MvGIsY8YxwMB2yDNvcE8wKbVLk1Wxu8AMGEC>    Dig into all this new functionality.    Watch this    Take a fun tour through agent building tech.    Here‚Äôs an excellent video that uses great imagery and code to clearly    explain concepts like agents, tools, and MCP.    A captured graphic of a Google Cloud video where Megan is explaining the    types of tools that ADK provides to agent builders.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5qmi5hPq_xU5g_nZdnEZnp_0L0Fa26W1KAjBgk4qAuvEcynLQKfeUov387stPuy86HHRtLSN49mcBKd14hQ7yV4ZUz2W-vMPj6gst7g7eTho1Gy8X1y32Vb4DBc1j4C31sgjATFVVsWNtwVtGWXypdR6uyrNO7_xw>    Community cuts    Send emails from Google Cloud using the Application Integration service.    It‚Äôs true we don‚Äôt offer a built-in managed email service. But you can    still send emails directly from your cloud apps using the Send Mail task    included in the Application Integration service. Learn more in this blog    post.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rnNhiNNKjLMH-w3cSwvlMWMgCN5zgCyYICdAM8b46bAHUxqScON231AMjD5LtmP9zIFkA4ijYJOoIJJl6UYR-jWmffJzZFQ77bixFsCfFI5pbQVL4ZjSO0ky3laUZX2nxRiYNAMTJ9WbaZZZ6MQG1z_ccqD5wl8RbDNwNvGF-G9GrYvGSzocDhxqD4kLDWmJHgShigklkJgd-M9_y40wTJfwqs4n6b8ISPQzUiGKJIiJ-BA6yNtIsCvxi4CxdUD4smQsIacYifJQxtfoIZeodu_BD0EHV1tvWUwCMQyGWhkESrsA>    Which service mesh is right for you?    It‚Äôs the age-old question: managed service or run it yourself? We give you    both options in Google Cloud. Rahul and Shrey compare the managed and    unmanaged flavors of Google Cloud Service Mesh.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5pjimu5L3TDZ8j8sRwCSyLgqf2lkEs5VV7ciYy4PQ9vyDta34hf-B2N0w917MEEQ-8kfOsEVD3U0hbOdhb99mMHowz3o3_mjIXY1xIU83n66UozwGeauzriU2OzG86X7ONyDVa2qlOcDZb8lAwKxDQi_JYa_M5txPrnxFWZx3eaeVe8ar-9X0nhicRRCH9PBN0tfA4vCelL2BZ9Tfg6LblJc6i1j1udKj70m7YrLeG15DJg45m2TcMP1qzZwgPUX37fBQAG1umki4BTI0UHlW7JBLu1qLmECtBewnXfYvbvaM0NQvw3iwC8BibwjMyPLgq6qprPKRdCPYE>    Building and evaluating ADK agents.    Our friends at W&B wrote up a good look at the Agent Development Kit    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rlAwPILlgbaPFdXN3DQNSQRwt64mfy9GpaHQD_eotncJyEGd6TBd6K7t_4GEEAN-XffNotncGbUFXRxSH7DmnblzGOgCpwPZ11k8868HWzXKB8XCy_f69mIMuMctc3_SoDUafg1E2oZXDkaw1-AFfIVsx_5jyJe94rEFLZ7LLKO9T0jfhq-zOaXrw6yfEkFeIYSJJnGXnfUV_Eu2ilAPfCHultJrTUZXlRCCBD8Bt9ZJF5ewdd-L-eA1JMNjCebH7YdVnjHybfRQYcdnmM7lKpE1W78Bfs1IHrsnMFr7YcfRoJ4ym6JrTZAzuJOQ>    and how you can trace their behavior.    Learn and grow    Try out Cloud Run worker pools by running this code lab.    We recently added this functionality to deploy continuously-processing    background workers to Cloud Run. This code lab walks you through creating    and using one as a Cloud Pub/Sub reader.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5qez7c1rh5fnKY3MncQ_GKFGLfbm7MIZ-E-1zm7B7sKFT_8CPmuuap7DqoAm774AtV1VxWM85a1jb9AfNblZ1Obtg_RpZP-HDfl7SioAJUIquJtMjITjjQpLq7Iw7cr_bn77ERGLhSDf_Fwq9-ntP_U4cbiRH9p8Ook-kTMGYiOQ8AyGq_57XHS1BkiVgjrdnU2VvopjgU9ujPDZbKjbGos07mCbTpM0QkDYjE3JhZMQ9Gg_1IglKX7ownOseyUQqClyqyOXAypE4k0I8p5X-UUYLv2MtQ8gOdxs-orK4wxAPo>    Build intelligent agents with the Agent Development Kit (ADK).    Today, we published a new course in Google Cloud Skills Boost for    developers ready to start building their own agents with    ADK.<https://c.gle/ANiao5qgY8SI2Em9PbFiHbfv088PKJEUz6B_50HqBWtY_sSyV5FZ0VhNiUrKJrd8hN1lmjTpGkh9O3NOWcreOS9QvNVA2upyBADIWT0YHfDC97SVH_BPaGZSIJeLk2MO8zio7qt6hgrUtjKtOwyg3tFfF_36dfOEGALGXuuS7SupTG9H5xdbf00-nicBNT1YcykrP_d-3o7DJNnq-BNCcnwmz59fhz4aQNF6137FUBQ0Xd2QvN9tsm1u>    It's packed with hands-on labs, core concepts, real-world applications, and    resources from Google Developer Experts (GDEs) and the broader developer    community.    Protect your (BigQuery) data from eager AI agents.    Here‚Äôs a great post with good tips for creating lines of defense around    your BigQuery environment    <https://c.gle/ANiao5obR_2-tdg0wZ4Gq82ZrS9EhM29j5YR4ACgcoFd2F_B6J4NX1W7H0ehdDe1-0mxKgVrUxeNrBu6SZ7jyGrMimdBuzZLOmOawlFr3rQsnZddFCJ8J4de2KKjYn2CxamiDIL-VDxgQOboLT46jgWI-LeQirzGj7CdD8FoaQOmEMPPPtab8e77VzNYgNJkcMK5Ftaoj7WhMEpCqutcmfoeIGjMeDtztgP3jTGxZIgJMQnoru0tsfp9E0Qds8-81UUA96-X-fmxkSDXgiK23e4mAEfpAHbX0MroXRxbC75PPau-dsKAFTtA9b31gHT95-cqvdIy>    to ensure agents don‚Äôt do too much, at too high a cost.    Get smart(er) about Google Cloud networking.    It‚Äôs hard to be good at Cloud without some working knowledge of networking    configurations. This quick reference guide    <https://c.gle/ANiao5otLo0jho4lkekyQOy-2-HeZoCKePTDKWnQ1JGrGS0ExvOY7IwrJ2ic3yAypAmEW-ly8je61PcAF4w0gy2-wxsluJLd1RKd9DiYXj6F8_0LeG8cfVsymLEyBwK8NZLUO14juwow9pBdkWbfBheQ7FBYrtoZBGjwwpDk-B5nJypBcArG9Y8lLyiYIO0izjHWh3ggCfpjJNYPDuOuBhpNmUXk-g8ICtSjVLOZxnliZMjNeV6C56oPMtCNk04HrIWGRk_JJsNHHjXF2n0xTA>    points you to assets that help you learn more.    Set up a GraphRAG setup with Vertex AI and Spanner Graph.    If you‚Äôve got graph data that you‚Äôd like to ground your AI applications    with, you might explore the GraphRAG option. I like this new comprehensive    architecture guide    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rNdUTRPpgDcWLOJhC3z5J7CLavFaxfi2WznzNF-cpL5KxKDt6RMStpV9aA6r4_W39cmaBOFP1m2YJjh9QJNh7ebJvBNrYj7lRR_AF-6uJ8P07TVazE_U2i3jWGrTVTqqsjiU7zpApu_8EimDO5ta8nQmtkneVMzrRX8HQf3lYAtI-mYgjInlb2E8cNorxy19-VfDeWhL514udoaClHZUTYkHbXxA>    that helps you configure this on Google Cloud.    Building production-ready AI Agents?    The Agent Factory video podcast dives deep into design, build, & deployment    on Google Cloud. The podcast covers code, architecture , & practical tips.    Subscribe now! ‚û°Ô∏è https://goo.gle/theagentfactory    <https://c.gle/ANiao5o1mzJ7wBd91tNCOVqScAgccfJHrYY0GWQ1QGNwM4HwnENIrhDcIdrVUyuBl0OozC7w-rPlWCubAiy6QWuLoJSJMay85-bMH9rkdg2ogVwu4EyvF33noZf-sDT7XEjuVMScSOl2761C6ELBwyxLnMDmV0gLP8fpnA>    One more thing    Batch mode comes to the Gemini API.    Large jobs where you don‚Äôt need an immediate response? The new Gemini API    Batch mode    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rvfu-Qk-zKRwHNy8mDUW4xxJp0S_8IINVuLg6YOTqvcGIdRVufCf-O9KRli6Wo4wcdbfK6mNuVscJR6rMglswv47nYa1oBp8XZ1NiCA7dm_4uz5Gk21iuvfVhZ6C8CilrCIpBAuBOZZu3FA5eKngrx6lfuyTgvupAC6H8otKA-HyDe2wmKQONJ2PY7v02QA7Y31juZodd62QcrxiIkWDC5ceO7IMatbcDOa5eugWk>    returns results within 24 hours, and is half the cost.    An X post from Logan announcing the new Batch mode in the Gemini API    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rMKOad2U3plkSgVYOVxixsYG4CSpNX-nMpVMXPoaRgFDBTTH3UQC46a_5v6WmHjFsg-i1OTH9-hJULJ9reD7WdrO5sWT92Xo-DvyezT01NZ-6swXX4j9ULzYSnfChccZCn69CkOehc8NMBe-Yt7cy_VcyTvgzAif9r4X3Md19zOt8eFh1UkA>    Follow us on Social media. subject: Google Cloud Career Launchpad Student Interest Form
text: Google Forms      Thanks for filling in Google Cloud Career Launchpad Student Interest Form  Here's what was received.    Edit response      Google Cloud Career Launchpad Student Interest Form    Thank you for your interest in the Google Cloud Career Launchpad    (previously Career Readiness) program. We have so much in store for you and    can't wait to have you onboard. üí™    What will you learn with the Google Cloud Career Launchpad program?  The Career Launchpad program is our effort to help students start a career    in the field of cloud and eventually get started with their first job or    internship. The program is ideal for students aspiring to launch careers in    engineering and management roles related to cloud infrastructure,    cloud-native application development, and data engineering.    Do I have to pay anything for the program?      Not at all! The learning content of the program is completely FREE OF COST    and Google will bear its cost for you.  On top of the learning content, we also provide 50% discount to students on    the OPTIONAl Google Cloud certifications which students can take if they    are interested otherwise can skip.    Get a chance to be shortlisted for Google Cloud Career Fair (India    ONLY) üë©‚Äçüíºüë®‚Äçüíº  And how can we forget - as part of the Career Launchpad program, you will    also get a chance to get shortlisted for the Google Cloud Career Fair that    we organise every year where we will help you get connected with potential    employers for a face-to-face interview opportunity towards your first job    or internship. üèÜ  (See below)      Email *      soham.k1804@gmail.com      Confirm your Email Address *    Please make sure that there are NO typos or errors in your email otherwise    you will not receive the email invitation to the program      soham.k1804@gmail.com      Google Cloud Career Fair (India ONLY)      Captionless Image      Terms & Conditions    ******  TERMS AND CONDITIONS    Google reserves the right to determine Your eligibility for the Google    Cloud Career Launchpad program.    By submitting this form, You, on behalf of yourself and the organization    you represent, if applicable, ('You') agree to these terms and conditions:    The credit is valid for Google Cloud training and certification and is    subject to Your acceptance of the applicable terms of service for the    training and certification platforms. The credit is non-transferable and    may not be sold or bartered. Unused credit expires on the date indicated on    the media conveying the credit information. The credit may be issued in    increments as You use the credit over the period of time during which the    credit is valid. Offer void where prohibited by law. The credits do not    have commercial value and may not be used for commercial purposes. Google    reserves the right to determine an individual's eligibility for training    and certification credits.    If You are a student, You represent that the credit can only be used in    Your capacity as a student of Your educational institution for skill    building and career development purposes and not for Your personal or hobby    use.    In addition, Credits may not be used to engage in mining cryptocurrency    unless You obtain Google's written consent in advance, which consent may be    revoked by Google in its discretion at any time.    You represent that (i) the credit is consistent with all applicable laws    and regulations, including relevant ethics rules and laws; (ii) the    provision of credits will not negatively impact Google's current or future    ability to do business with your educational institution, (iii) You are not    a resident of a US embargoed country, (v) You are not ordinarily a resident    in a US embargoed country, and (iv) You are not otherwise prohibited by    applicable export controls and sanctions programs from participating in the    credit redemption program.    Communication & Tracking  * Google may contact you via email to provision benefits and send surveys    and other communication related to the Google Cloud Career Launchpad    program.  * By joining, you agree to Google Cloud Training & the faculty members of    your institution tracking your grades and other activity in the learning    program.  * By joining, you agree to share your contact information with the faculty    members of your institution so that they can reach out to you and help    during the learning program.      I have read the above terms *      Yes, I accept the terms      I decline (By declining, you will not receive the invitation for the    program)      Fill out your details    We are so happy that you have made it here and are interested in taking    part in the Google Cloud Career Launchpad program. Please take a minute and    fill out your details below so that we can onboard you to the program and    send you enrolment instructions      Your full name *      Soham Chetan Kulkarni      Your contact number    We collect this information to share this with potential employers in the    future when you graduate.  Note: This is an OPTIONAL field, if you do not wish to share your contact    number, please leave it blank.      8805814877      Gender *      Male        Select your institution from the list below *      Shri Vithal Education & Research Institute        If selected 'Others' above, then specify your institution name      Select your current academic year *      First Year      Second Year      Third Year      Fourth Year      Fifth Year & above      Graduated      In which year are you graduating/graduated? *    For Example: 2023, 2024, 2025, etc.      2026      Do you have access to a working internet connection and a laptop with    latest chrome browser? *    Note: This is a minimum requirement for you to participate in the program.      Yes      No      Do you have an account on Google Cloud Skills Boost -    https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/? *      Yes, I already have an account      No, i want to create one      Submit your Google Cloud Skills Boost Profile URL    Great! You have a Google Cloud Skills Boost account. Please do remember to    share your profile below so that we can track your progress in the program    and send you your prizes when you win      Log-in to https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/ if not already logged in  Once logged-in, then go to https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/profile/.  Now click on the red underlined button 'Make profile public' below your    account picture and then click 'Make Profile Public' if there's a pop-up.    (See screenshot below)  Give some time for the page to load. Once it loads, you will be on your    profile page. Now just share the URL displayed there. (That's your profile    URL)  Here is a small video (just 1 minute) that will walk you through how to do    this and get your profile URL - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C7Zb3cqEkwA  (You can watch it at 2x speed to go faster)        (If the above video doesn't work for you, then refer to this video instead    - https://youtu.be/uFvfMngxYXQ?si=gU2cB3roVVbv_l3l)      Get your GCSB Public Profile URL    Captionless Image      [VERY IMPORTANT] Please share your Google Cloud Skills Boost Public Profile    URL (See how to get your profile URL-    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C7Zb3cqEkwA) *    Here's what it should look like -    https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/public_profiles/PROFILE_ID  (DO NOT copy-paste this as your application will be REJECTED)      https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/public_profiles/d6aaf7ba-cca8-41e3-995c-b1f7035193df      I understand that if I submitted a wrong profile URL above then I will NOT    receive the invitation to the program *      ‚úì  I understand      Select your track for the program    We have 5 different tracks in the program that your faculty member(s) have    chosen from. Based on what your faculty has chosen, you need to select the    same track below so that you can be assigned to their group on Google Cloud    Skills boost and receive the invitation for the program.        Note:        It might be possible that they are multiple faculty members in your    institution and they have chosen either 1 or 2 or all the 5 tracks. So    before selecting your own track below, please reach out to your faculty and    confirm the track(s) they have opted for and then make your selection. If    you already know this, then please go ahead and select the track.  Also, each student can choose only 1 track. We have provided some    information below for all the 5 tracks. Please read the same VERY CAREFULLY    before you make the selection. Once invited, you will NOT be allowed to    change your track.      For more information, please feel free to reach out to your faculty    directly.      See information about all the 6 tracks below    Here are the available tracks in the program and some information about    them that would help you make a decision of which one to select:        Cloud Engineering Certificate (ACE)  You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students who have little to no experience    with cloud computing and want to start from scratch.  See the content and curriculum for the ACE track here. It consists of ~80    hours of content with 6 on-demand courses and 4 lab-based courses (skill    badges).  [Optional Offering] Associate Cloud Engineer exam is also part of this    track as OPTIONAL. Students who successfully complete the training get a    50% discount and faculty members get a 100% discount on the 1st attempt of    the exam.  Cloud Digital Leader Course Series (CDL)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students with business backgrounds like    MBA and wants to understand the business aspects of cloud  See the content and curriculum for the CDL track here. It consists of ~9    hours of content with 6 on-demand courses.  [Optional Offering] Cloud Digital Leader exam is also part of this track as    OPTIONAL. Students who successfully complete the training get a 50%    discount and faculty members get a 100% discount on the 1st attempt of the    exam.  Data Analytics Certificate (ADP)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students who have keen interest in data    analysis.  See the content and curriculum for the DA track here. It consists of ~90    hours of content with 4 on-demand courses + 1 Capstone project at the end +    1 preparatory course for Associate Data Practitioner exam.  [Optional Offering] Associate Data Practitioner exam is also part of this    track as OPTIONAL. Students who successfully complete the training get a    50% discount and faculty members get a 100% discount on the 1st attempt of    the exam.  Cloud Cybersecurity Certificate (CYBER)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This track is generally right for students who have keen interest in cloud    based security and helps prepare learners for roles like Developer Security    Operations.  See the content and curriculum for the CYBER track here. It consists of ~90    hours of content with 4 on-demand courses + 1 Capstone project at the end.  No global level certification offered in this track yet.  Generative AI Course Series (GAIL)    You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This 2 course pathway series helps learners build expertise in generative    AI and its fundamentals ranging from large language models, responsible AI    and Gemini as well.  See the content and curriculum for all 2 pathways of the AI track here &    here. It consists of ~30 hours of content with 2 on-demand courses    consisting of 1 skill badge credential.  No global level certification offered in this track yet.    Google Cloud Computing Foundations (GCCF)      You can find out more information about the track in our deck here. Points    to note:        This certificate program provides individuals with little to no background    or experience in cloud computing a detailed overview of concepts covering    cloud basics, big data, machine learning, and where and how Google Cloud    fits in.  See the content and curriculum for the GCCF track here. It consists of ~40    hours of content with 4 on-demand courses + 4 lab-based courses.  No global level certification offered in this track yet.        Select your track for the program *    Please make sure to read the information above for each track before moving    forward.      Cloud Engineering Certificate (ACE)      Cloud Digital Leader Course Series (CDL)      Data Analytics Certificate (ADP)      Cloud Cybersecurity Certificate (CYBER)      Generative AI Course Series (GAIL)      Google Cloud Computing Foundations (GCCF)      I acknowledge that if I selected a track that is not opted by my faculty    members, then I would be by default assigned to the ACE track or the track    they have opted for if its not the ACE track. *      I acknowledge      [README] What should you expect after you submit the form?    Once you submit the form, we will check:      Whether you have submitted the right profile URL or not. If not, then you    will have to go back and fill the form again otherwise you will not receive    the program invitation.  Whether the deadline for your institution has passed or not. Only those    submissions will be counted which were made during the institution deadline.  Once the above conditions are met, we will confirm your participation from    your faculty and will send you the program invitation.    In case of any queries, do remember to reach out to your faculty member.      Create your own Google Form    Does this form look suspicious? Report

subject: Funds/Securities Balance
text:
Dear Investor,

With reference to NSE circulars NSE/INSP/46704 dated December 17, 2020, and NSE/INSP/55039 dated December 28, 2022, Trading members are required to upload clients' securities balance on a daily basis.

Further, with reference to NCL circular NCL/CMPL/49348 dated Aug 20, 2021, and NSE circular NSE/INSP/49691 dated September 22, 2021, Members are required to upload disaggregated collateral information (segment-wise and asset type wise) at the client level to their Clearing corporations on a daily basis.

Information pertaining to your fund and securities balance as on {{last_date_of_saturday}} provided by {{tm_name}} along with the details of securities ISIN wise is attached.

Please follow the procedure given below for opening the attachment:

  1. Click on the attachment provided with this mail.
  2. You will be prompted for your password.
  3. The password is your PAN number in upper case.

Please note that negative number in the file represents debit balance/balance payable by you. Also, the funds and securities balances provided are what is maintained with your broker and does not include balance in your personal bank account and demat account.

You are advised to compare the funds, securities and commodities balances received from Exchange on a weekly basis with the balances in the weekly statement of accounts for funds, securities and commodities sent by the stockbroker for the respective date. In case you find any discrepancy in the balances, we advise you to take up the matter immediately with your Broker.You may contact customer service at {{tm_email_id}} or {{tm_contact_no}}.

In case of non-resolution of discrepancy by the broker, you may intimate the same to the Exchange at ignse@nse.co.in or 18002660050 or register an online complaint at https://smartodr.in/login.

The data is being provided to the clients on an 'as is' and 'what-is' basis as provided by the trading member. The Exchange shall not be liable for any delays, errors, omissions, commissions, inaccuracies in rendering the data. In no event shall the Exchange be liable for any damages, including without limitation direct or indirect, special, incidental, or consequential damages, losses or expenses arising in connection with the data provided by the Exchange through this facility.

You are requested to note that in the event of trading member being declared as defaulter/expelled, all transactions executed on the exchange trading platform within 90 calendar days prior to the effective date of disablement of the trading member or after the latest monthly/quarterly settlement date, if any, in respect of the claimant whichever is later shall be considered eligible for compensation from IPFT subject to Rules, Byelaws, Regulations, guidelines etc. of the Exchange and SEBI circulars and subject to the appropriate norms laid down by the relevant Committee. For details, you may refer the policy hosted on the website https://static.nseindia.com//s3fs-public/inline-files/Policy_for_evaluation_of_claims_0.pdf

For Information & Education Purpose

We would like to draw your attention to 'SEBI vide circular dated April 04, 2022, wherein they have introduced the mechanism of ‚ÄúDemat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI)‚Äù. The DDPI shall serve the same purpose of POA and significantly mitigate the misuse of POA. You should be aware that the stockbroker and depository participant cannot directly / indirectly compel the clients to execute the DDPI or deny services to the client if the client refuses to execute the DDPI.

Please refer to SEBI Circular dated October 06, 2022, for the list of instructions which client can give to its stockbroker / depository participant. You may refer the following link for same: https://www.sebi.gov.in/legal/circulars/oct-2022/execution-of-demat-debit-and-pledge-instruction-ddpi-for-transfer-of-securities-towards-deliveries-settlement-obligations-and-pledging-re-pledging-of-securities-clarification_63724.html Should you wish to give any instructions, these need to be signed in physical against each purpose of DDPI. In case of an eSign option is made available, client should be given an option to choose the specific purpose(s) of DDPI'.

Dos and Don‚Äôts for Retail Investors:
  1. Please deal with SEBI registered intermediaries only. Ensure that you have complete knowledge of the products and the risks involved before investing.
  2. Offering fixed/guaranteed/regular returns/ capital protection schemes in stock markets whether written or oral is not allowed. Brokers or any of their representatives or Authorised Persons cannot enter into any loan agreement to pay interest on the funds/securities offered by you.
  3. Do not fall prey to emails, SMSs and online videos luring you to trade in stock/ securities / schemes promising high returns/profits.
  4. Ensure to fill all the required details in the 'KYC' document by yourself and receive duly signed copy of your 'KYC' documents from your broker.
  5. Trading in derivatives involves high risk and accordingly investors should understand the product well before trading in such segments/products.
  6. Opt for electronic (e-mail) contract notes/financial statements only if you are computer savvy and have your own e-mail account.
  7. Do not share your login ID, password, OTP, TPIN with any person including employees of the broker or Authorised Person under any circumstances.
  8. Ensure that all your trades are executed as per your instructions.
  9. Insure you receive the payout of funds and securities within 1 working day of settlement. In case you have chosen running account of funds, ensure your account is settled on first Friday/Saturday of every month / quarter as opted for.
  10. Dealing in cash is prohibited. Do not place any securities with the broker or associate of the broker or authorized person of the broker. Do not transfer securities as margin/ collateral to the broker and such securities only must be pledged from the client demat account.
  11. Opt for Demat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI) only for transfer of securities for deliveries/settlement obligations, initiating pledging of securities for margins, and for mutual fund/open offer transactions on Exchange platform. DDPI/PoA are optional and should not be insisted on for opening the account.
  12. Always keep your mobile number and email id updated with your broker. Don't ignore any SMSs / e-mails with regards to contract notes/trades/funds and securities balances sent by broker/Exchange. Verify the details of the same and report discrepancy, if any, to your broker in writing immediately.
  13. Please verify the bank account details of the broker from the website of broker/Exchange before transferring funds to the broker.
  14. Claims for funds or securities given to the broker under any arrangement/ agreement of indicative return or claims for funds, without transactions on the Exchange will not be accepted by the Exchange in case of default by your broker.
  15. For more details on Investor awareness, please visit-www.nseindia.com/invest/investors-home
  16. For more information related to investments in securities market, please visit SEBI Investor Website - https://investor.sebi.gov.in and SEBI Saa‚Çπthi Mobile App.

We are glad to inform you that NSE for your convenience/comfort is providing links below on investment concepts, investor alerts, your rights and obligation as an investor.

www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-know-your-rights
www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-fraud-dos-and-donts
www.nseindia.com/invest/file-a-complaint-online

You may also visit our website www.nseindia.com for any further information that you may require or email your queries to the email ID ignse@nse.co.in, quoting the name of your city in the subject. We would be glad to assist you.

Information to investors:

Exchange has introduced trading in Rights Entitlement w.e.f. May 20, 2020. The trades executed, if any, for Rights Entitlement in Capital Market shall form part of the attached file. Rights Entitlement should not be mistaken for ordinary shares and unless Rights Entitlement are exercised they will lose value and no rights (shares) will be available to the investor. The buyer of the Rights Entitlement is required to subscribe for the same before the Issue Closing Date, else the same will lapse and no shares will be allotted.

In case you need any clarification, please feel free to call on our toll-free number 1800 266 0050 (select option 5 - UCI & Trade Alerts). You can also email us at uci@nse.co.in, quoting your PAN, Mobile no. and your query.

To learn more about Personal Finance, securities market, details of upcoming Investor Awareness Programs and more, please visit the SEBI Investor website at https://investor.sebi.gov.in

Thanks and Regards,
National Stock Exchange of India Limited

Missed Your SIP? Don't Worry, Pay Now.

subject: Funds/Securities Balance
text:
Dear Investor,

With reference to NSE circulars NSE/INSP/46704 dated December 17, 2020, and NSE/INSP/55039 dated December 28, 2022, Trading members are required to upload clients' securities balance on a daily basis.

Further, with reference to NCL circular NCL/CMPL/49348 dated Aug 20, 2021, and NSE circular NSE/INSP/49691 dated September 22, 2021, Members are required to upload disaggregated collateral information (segment-wise and asset type wise) at the client level to their Clearing corporations on a daily basis.

Information pertaining to your fund and securities balance as on {{last_date_of_saturday}} provided by {{tm_name}} along with the details of securities ISIN wise is attached.

Please follow the procedure given below for opening the attachment:

  1. Click on the attachment provided with this mail.
  2. You will be prompted for your password.
  3. The password is your PAN number in upper case.

Please note that negative number in the file represents debit balance/balance payable by you. Also, the funds and securities balances provided are what is maintained with your broker and does not include balance in your personal bank account and demat account.

You are advised to compare the funds, securities and commodities balances received from Exchange on a weekly basis with the balances in the weekly statement of accounts for funds, securities and commodities sent by the stockbroker for the respective date. In case you find any discrepancy in the balances, we advise you to take up the matter immediately with your Broker.You may contact customer service at {{tm_email_id}} or {{tm_contact_no}}.

In case of non-resolution of discrepancy by the broker, you may intimate the same to the Exchange at ignse@nse.co.in or 18002660050 or register an online complaint at https://smartodr.in/login.

The data is being provided to the clients on an 'as is' and 'what-is' basis as provided by the trading member. The Exchange shall not be liable for any delays, errors, omissions, commissions, inaccuracies in rendering the data. In no event shall the Exchange be liable for any damages, including without limitation direct or indirect, special, incidental, or consequential damages, losses or expenses arising in connection with the data provided by the Exchange through this facility.

You are requested to note that in the event of trading member being declared as defaulter/expelled, all transactions executed on the exchange trading platform within 90 calendar days prior to the effective date of disablement of the trading member or after the latest monthly/quarterly settlement date, if any, in respect of the claimant whichever is later shall be considered eligible for compensation from IPFT subject to Rules, Byelaws, Regulations, guidelines etc. of the Exchange and SEBI circulars and subject to the appropriate norms laid down by the relevant Committee. For details, you may refer the policy hosted on the website https://static.nseindia.com//s3fs-public/inline-files/Policy_for_evaluation_of_claims_0.pdf

For Information & Education Purpose

We would like to draw your attention to 'SEBI vide circular dated April 04, 2022, wherein they have introduced the mechanism of ‚ÄúDemat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI)‚Äù. The DDPI shall serve the same purpose of POA and significantly mitigate the misuse of POA. You should be aware that the stockbroker and depository participant cannot directly / indirectly compel the clients to execute the DDPI or deny services to the client if the client refuses to execute the DDPI.

Please refer to SEBI Circular dated October 06, 2022, for the list of instructions which client can give to its stockbroker / depository participant. You may refer the following link for same: https://www.sebi.gov.in/legal/circulars/oct-2022/execution-of-demat-debit-and-pledge-instruction-ddpi-for-transfer-of-securities-towards-deliveries-settlement-obligations-and-pledging-re-pledging-of-securities-clarification_63724.html Should you wish to give any instructions, these need to be signed in physical against each purpose of DDPI. In case of an eSign option is made available, client should be given an option to choose the specific purpose(s) of DDPI'.

Dos and Don‚Äôts for Retail Investors:
  1. Please deal with SEBI registered intermediaries only. Ensure that you have complete knowledge of the products and the risks involved before investing.
  2. Offering fixed/guaranteed/regular returns/ capital protection schemes in stock markets whether written or oral is not allowed. Brokers or any of their representatives or Authorised Persons cannot enter into any loan agreement to pay interest on the funds/securities offered by you.
  3. Do not fall prey to emails, SMSs and online videos luring you to trade in stock/ securities / schemes promising high returns/profits.
  4. Ensure to fill all the required details in the 'KYC' document by yourself and receive duly signed copy of your 'KYC' documents from your broker.
  5. Trading in derivatives involves high risk and accordingly investors should understand the product well before trading in such segments/products.
  6. Opt for electronic (e-mail) contract notes/financial statements only if you are computer savvy and have your own e-mail account.
  7. Do not share your login ID, password, OTP, TPIN with any person including employees of the broker or Authorised Person under any circumstances.
  8. Ensure that all your trades are executed as per your instructions.
  9. Insure you receive the payout of funds and securities within 1 working day of settlement. In case you have chosen running account of funds, ensure your account is settled on first Friday/Saturday of every month / quarter as opted for.
  10. Dealing in cash is prohibited. Do not place any securities with the broker or associate of the broker or authorized person of the broker. Do not transfer securities as margin/ collateral to the broker and such securities only must be pledged from the client demat account.
  11. Opt for Demat Debit and Pledge Instruction (DDPI) only for transfer of securities for deliveries/settlement obligations, initiating pledging of securities for margins, and for mutual fund/open offer transactions on Exchange platform. DDPI/PoA are optional and should not be insisted on for opening the account.
  12. Always keep your mobile number and email id updated with your broker. Don't ignore any SMSs / e-mails with regards to contract notes/trades/funds and securities balances sent by broker/Exchange. Verify the details of the same and report discrepancy, if any, to your broker in writing immediately.
  13. Please verify the bank account details of the broker from the website of broker/Exchange before transferring funds to the broker.
  14. Claims for funds or securities given to the broker under any arrangement/ agreement of indicative return or claims for funds, without transactions on the Exchange will not be accepted by the Exchange in case of default by your broker.
  15. For more details on Investor awareness, please visit-www.nseindia.com/invest/investors-home
  16. For more information related to investments in securities market, please visit SEBI Investor Website - https://investor.sebi.gov.in and SEBI Saa‚Çπthi Mobile App.
