We are glad to inform you that NSE for your convenience/comfort is providing links below on investment concepts, investor alerts, your rights and obligation as an investor.

www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-know-your-rights
www.nseindia.com/invest/first-time-investor-fraud-dos-and-donts
www.nseindia.com/invest/file-a-complaint-online

You may also visit our website www.nseindia.com for any further information that you may require or email your queries to the email ID ignse@nse.co.in, quoting the name of your city in the subject. We would be glad to assist you.

Information to investors:

Exchange has introduced trading in Rights Entitlement w.e.f. May 20, 2020. The trades executed, if any, for Rights Entitlement in Capital Market shall form part of the attached file. Rights Entitlement should not be mistaken for ordinary shares and unless Rights Entitlement are exercised they will lose value and no rights (shares) will be available to the investor. The buyer of the Rights Entitlement is required to subscribe for the same before the Issue Closing Date, else the same will lapse and no shares will be allotted.

In case you need any clarification, please feel free to call on our toll-free number 1800 266 0050 (select option 5 - UCI & Trade Alerts). You can also email us at uci@nse.co.in, quoting your PAN, Mobile no. and your query.

To learn more about Personal Finance, securities market, details of upcoming Investor Awareness Programs and more, please visit the SEBI Investor website at https://investor.sebi.gov.in

Thanks and Regards,
National Stock Exchange of India Limited

text: https://flutterflow.io/      ** üå≥ Branching Improvements  ------------------------------------------------------------    We know branching can be tricky‚Äîespecially for big projects with lots of contributors. We‚Äôre actively working to make it faster and smoother.    While there‚Äôs still more to do (performance is a key focus), here are some recent improvements:  * Better Navigation: Filter by category in the merge sidebar and use advanced search (Match Case, Match Whole Word, or top-level only).  * Smarter Merging: We‚Äôve improved merge speed, especially for projects with lots of translations. We also use Git to better detect unchanged files.  * Less Stale Branches: You‚Äôll now see a stale branch dialog when trying to merge a branch that‚Äôs been hanging around for longer than a week.  * Safer Conflict Resolution: When resolving a conflict, you can now Copy Nested Files, which helps keep your components intact and prevents broken dependencies.  * Heads Up: We removed the option to duplicate a project with branches since that flow led to unexpected behavior for some users.        ** ‚úÖ Bulk User Management  ------------------------------------------------------------    You can now bulk invite team members to a project and update their roles all at once‚Äîno more one-by-one clicks.    Paste a list of emails (comma-separated or line-separated), and FlutterFlow will automatically detect and format them for you to make it easy to invite them.    Use checkboxes to select multiple users and adjust their access levels in bulk. If the selected users have different access levels, we‚Äôll show the options that are available to everyone (for example, you can remove access from all selected users or downgrade them to Read-only if that‚Äôs valid).    This works with search, filters, and sorting too‚Äîso you can easily find just the group you want to update.        ** ‚ôø Focus Borders  ------------------------------------------------------------    We‚Äôve added focus borders to make your apps easier to navigate with keyboards or assistive technologies.    How to use it:  * Add an action to a widget  * Go to the widget‚Äôs Accessibility options  * Toggle Show Border on Focus  * Customize the Border Width, Color, and Radius to match your design      ** üõ†Ô∏è Other Improvements  ------------------------------------------------------------  * Wait (Delay) action now accepts variable duration.  * Added /listPartitionedFileFields endpoint to Project API to list all possible fields (not nested) for a given filename.  * Updated AI Agent models to stable versions of Gemini 2.5 Pro and Flash.  * Disabled WASM in Test Mode to improve reload performance.  * Enhanced text scaling to automatically respect device accessibility settings when app-level scaling is at default, while maintaining priority for explicit in-app text scaling controls.      **  üêû Bug Fixes  ------------------------------------------------------------  * Fixed an issue where Test Mode would not display error messages on build failures.  * Fixed iOS Local Run issues with Firebase App Check enforcement by enabling iOS App Check debug tokens.  * Fixed an issue when deploying CORS proxy functions via Firebase.  * Fixed an issue where loops within action callback parameters did not function correctly.  * Fixed an issue where accessing parent loop values from a nested loop failed.  * Fixed an issue where Loop over List operations failed in Action Blocks.  * Fixed JSON path operations incorrectly converting Map objects to strings, which was causing crashes when trying to parse nested JSON data into custom data types.  * Fixed an issue that blocked renaming of DataTables.  * Fixed an issue where library page routes would not be updated correctly if the route was never overridden.  * Fixed an issue with Supabase streaming where query results were not accessible in On Data Change actions.  * Fixed the visibility of the 'Generate with AI' button in the page selection panel.  * Fixed an issue where the first element of a RichText could not be edited.  * Fixed an issue where projects would be updated even if custom files hadn‚Äôt changed.  * Fixed an issue with playing asset audio on Android.  * Fixed an issue with build.gradle not consistently updating when unlocked.  * Fixed an issue where invalid variables could be inappropriately set.  * Fixed an issue where package.json could not be edited in the Cloud Functions tab.  * Fixed an issue where AppDelegate.swift changes would not reflect in exported code.      ** üöÄ ICYMI: DreamFlow  ------------------------------------------------------------    The next evolution of DreamFlow is here and available at www.dreamflow.app (http://www.dreamflow.app/) . DreamFlow now gives you the power to edit visually, write code, or let the agent handle changes for you. You‚Äôll see a sharper experience that lets you:    ‚Ä¢ Start with a prompt to break the blank page  ‚Ä¢ Build visually with intuitive controls  ‚Ä¢ Refine with precision in real code    This is tri-surface development - agentic, visual, and code - built for speed, flexibility, and full control. Watch Dreamflow in action (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yN15o1F8dic) .      ** üèóÔ∏è New Features We're Working On  ------------------------------------------------------------  * An AI chatbot that uses context from our internal Technical Support Team to provide answers to you instantly.  * MCP support  * Building some exciting product updates for FFDC 2025 (https://www.ffdc.io/) !    Have a Technical Question or Issue?  If you need help building in FlutterFlow, you can sign up for office hours with one of our Developer Relations Team members here (https://calendly.com/d/ck9k-hzz-ywc/flutterflow-devrel-office-hours?month=2024-10) .    ============================================================  ** FlutterFlow Logo (https://flutterflow.io)    Build Different.    You are receiving this email because you signed up on ** flutterflow.io (https://flutterflow.io)  ** YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC5LueiosDVInA6yXE_38i9Q)  ** Twitter (http://www.twitter.com/flutterflow)  ** LinkedIn (https://www.linkedin.com/company/flutterflow)  ** Website (https://www.flutterflow.io)  ¬© 2025 FlutterFlow, Inc.    Our mailing address:  883 N Shoreline Blvd, #B220,  Mountain View, CA 94043    Want to change how you receive these emails?  You can ** update your preferences (https://flutterflow.us2.list-manage.com/profile?u=544d5264f5e71e5fa379d41f5&id=43c1c0eebb&e=0a9d458d40&c=f672fbbfcc)  or ** unsubscribe from this list (https://flutterflow.us2.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=544d5264f5e71e5fa379d41f5&id=43c1c0eebb&t=b&e=0a9d458d40&c=f672fbbfcc)  .

text: Kaggle                  Hi Soham C Kulkarni,    At Kaggle, we believe in the power of community-driven evaluation. That's    why we're thrilled to introduce Kaggle Benchmarks, our new platform making    it easier for anyone to test and understand model capabilities.    To showcase the platform, we are unveiling the ICML 2025 AI Experts    Benchmark crowdsourced at the ICML conference in Vancouver. We evaluated    over 30 tasks that reflect the real-world interests of AI researchers and    industry experts on leading models, including Gemini 2.5 Pro, Claude 4    Sonnet, o4 mini, and DeepSeek-R1.      Kaggle Benchmarks Platform with metrics, leaderboards, and customization    options        Want to create your own evals to test models at no cost or infrastructure    setup? Join the waitlist for early access to custom task creation! Plus,    check out kaggle.com/benchmarks featuring 70+ leaderboards like SciCode,    GPQA, and Meta's new MultiLoKo benchmark. The Kaggle Team        Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043    This email was sent to soham.k1804@gmail.com because you indicated that    you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. text: The overwhelmed person‚Äôs guide to Google Cloud By Richard Seroter    <mailto:rseroter@google.com>    New and shiny    Your agents got an upgrade with the new Vertex AI Agent Engine Memory Bank.    Our interactions with agents may span sessions and extend for some time.    You‚Äôve had to solve this with your own state solutions. But with the new    Memory Bank, you get a managed service that ‚Äújust works‚Äù for agents running    in Vertex AI Agent Engine. See the blog post    <https://c.gle/ANiao5o0sWOF9wVgO7HNzhO0XqPUcrk1gFCiZa1lgCUCSO0BDgxwJm6_12gADn4OTJj1_U7YMWWLSl95VqN4QeZr_Q6RFe7bwlchvpgOP6HxK5FC9BWJJNB4j2lVEWFCdPiRgcvoOF8cIhpa6BaqaWYySZI_zAiuC_M318aKeYj8JtOBNq5yHLIH2GjzH1cGkN5whywmiKj486bbXL_WSlTNBO1BkgJ9lNMuAoIW6UqYiFGwP3Jp>    and docs    <https://c.gle/ANiao5pFGBFD-KEHWDR6WDVFPcW2TFA4_EUb3TnN_XQcdd0uFwCXMEbSFADP9rGagE_YvPephDiqSFaTZZCl957XV9cxg0NhZJvPRaoLWhMnpa1XLt3OfvhvMfogN8mAm8BiFDM5v5oe6eLoIGmRHjEMS3Ja6JWKqgmNCA0u5tIQZwqA1V0yxQZcJI5d2wB4QRjIV5n1Doyr6VKtOA-6Bz-Zdzi3UaVu>    for more.    BigQuery gets some powerful new aggregation functions.    This won‚Äôt appeal to all of you, but to those dealing with rich data sets,    this might be a BIG deal. These three new categories of aggregation    functions    <https://c.gle/ANiao5pl2STjtSRbavUedgpGaWjaOZ3f2K3o0YF_5xrIjcUNECZWV3KAEIGc8kJT_i506eAbxiPPMUSGd00g-XZjJIHFAoGQ53J0D60O2VTf-ryNjCKsnaXdHNtMhcQKxFPRJ5ae9UoU-qgOpTJg5hy2unz9AU-6D78zm9elyGWDMn-QLLIHMBy2HUjHy3PqpnCWHpK-JaU5ZZ2GmgTwMFrHrxfqHknEb4JRTvBDsVPgbxil_hNQLiFNeRXElVRH3ItGwMTqJehcfP2z5Lax1Tcj>‚Äîgroup    by extension, user-defined aggregation functions, and approximate aggregate    functions‚Äîmay introduce massive performance and efficiency improvements.    Cloud Run introduces worker pools and new Docker integrations.    How do you deploy a background task that continuously chomps on work? Now    you can run these in Cloud Run worker    pools.<https://c.gle/ANiao5o9H-3zuxG4hU2DH5L8erWG9SsfoFi1sddeejVXg0BO1pnmQlB1GuQCgIyNDwo8IeoTz2xmLnaT6qirETyOFug8_EllT-KlViCDOHb0Qb3lzry8WhMk_vvyUdkR8syPubVKRfBsxb7Qs7zONzMWBhfmvL4tlvg33DgyCEjefFl20aR7VDpyN48NY9kLVGAGzhI>    It‚Äôs great for processing data from Apache Kafka, and we also introduced a    new open source Cloud Run Kafka Autoscaler.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5qcqU2bh2Wa1TewB06osRAmhUbqteo8lt4xiceDIA7Bz_KaeIGDNlSumh8d4qBSdqZAL0ely_TadzfjlGevuGE_TAj_ACtIBjsJgqdFPNChlk7HlL_8bmaF0c-uGPjhbzQBZSDEQAaXeYUF5mKDOp_yPVR4XAnRb8y097dQy2AZzlt_iL-tKBN3bs2p1AMHdWhOLDJiSNKqSPfAQKT6oIt10ofXmsOp1qhan_VczQQcXZytfKtJQbNre5qk5Q>    We also shared new integrations that make it easier to deploy Docker    Compose definitions to Cloud    Run.<https://c.gle/ANiao5p530S1bwilAsm7eGmrob9f7Pu_nNMYTw3qppcRgh-9JPb5hqFUDi8rR1UuL8RKYjDywbpUgkTHOP3fmjwLxvujFZ457R97JcFKygSnFBon4ErQSWrBoLd70jWrFf8LIAfBHo4nFkFRXcl3xJhqlo9JmGiAWZJ1p_FpEPxDCtsU_Yi5dan9RYUlAgL6-s33u74QwoD7crY0EVWynK1NmCRwoJePAXizL2QYO0iH20TrNt48MvGIsY8YxwMB2yDNvcE8wKbVLk1Wxu8AMGEC>    Dig into all this new functionality.    Watch this    Take a fun tour through agent building tech.    Here‚Äôs an excellent video that uses great imagery and code to clearly    explain concepts like agents, tools, and MCP.    A captured graphic of a Google Cloud video where Megan is explaining the    types of tools that ADK provides to agent builders.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5qmi5hPq_xU5g_nZdnEZnp_0L0Fa26W1KAjBgk4qAuvEcynLQKfeUov387stPuy86HHRtLSN49mcBKd14hQ7yV4ZUz2W-vMPj6gst7g7eTho1Gy8X1y32Vb4DBc1j4C31sgjATFVVsWNtwVtGWXypdR6uyrNO7_xw>    Community cuts    Send emails from Google Cloud using the Application Integration service.    It‚Äôs true we don‚Äôt offer a built-in managed email service. But you can    still send emails directly from your cloud apps using the Send Mail task    included in the Application Integration service. Learn more in this blog    post.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rnNhiNNKjLMH-w3cSwvlMWMgCN5zgCyYICdAM8b46bAHUxqScON231AMjD5LtmP9zIFkA4ijYJOoIJJl6UYR-jWmffJzZFQ77bixFsCfFI5pbQVL4ZjSO0ky3laUZX2nxRiYNAMTJ9WbaZZZ6MQG1z_ccqD5wl8RbDNwNvGF-G9GrYvGSzocDhxqD4kLDWmJHgShigklkJgd-M9_y40wTJfwqs4n6b8ISPQzUiGKJIiJ-BA6yNtIsCvxi4CxdUD4smQsIacYifJQxtfoIZeodu_BD0EHV1tvWUwCMQyGWhkESrsA>    Which service mesh is right for you?    It‚Äôs the age-old question: managed service or run it yourself? We give you    both options in Google Cloud. Rahul and Shrey compare the managed and    unmanaged flavors of Google Cloud Service Mesh.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5pjimu5L3TDZ8j8sRwCSyLgqf2lkEs5VV7ciYy4PQ9vyDta34hf-B2N0w917MEEQ-8kfOsEVD3U0hbOdhb99mMHowz3o3_mjIXY1xIU83n66UozwGeauzriU2OzG86X7ONyDVa2qlOcDZb8lAwKxDQi_JYa_M5txPrnxFWZx3eaeVe8ar-9X0nhicRRCH9PBN0tfA4vCelL2BZ9Tfg6LblJc6i1j1udKj70m7YrLeG15DJg45m2TcMP1qzZwgPUX37fBQAG1umki4BTI0UHlW7JBLu1qLmECtBewnXfYvbvaM0NQvw3iwC8BibwjMyPLgq6qprPKRdCPYE>    Building and evaluating ADK agents.    Our friends at W&B wrote up a good look at the Agent Development Kit    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rlAwPILlgbaPFdXN3DQNSQRwt64mfy9GpaHQD_eotncJyEGd6TBd6K7t_4GEEAN-XffNotncGbUFXRxSH7DmnblzGOgCpwPZ11k8868HWzXKB8XCy_f69mIMuMctc3_SoDUafg1E2oZXDkaw1-AFfIVsx_5jyJe94rEFLZ7LLKO9T0jfhq-zOaXrw6yfEkFeIYSJJnGXnfUV_Eu2ilAPfCHultJrTUZXlRCCBD8Bt9ZJF5ewdd-L-eA1JMNjCebH7YdVnjHybfRQYcdnmM7lKpE1W78Bfs1IHrsnMFr7YcfRoJ4ym6JrTZAzuJOQ>    and how you can trace their behavior.    Learn and grow    Try out Cloud Run worker pools by running this code lab.    We recently added this functionality to deploy continuously-processing    background workers to Cloud Run. This code lab walks you through creating    and using one as a Cloud Pub/Sub reader.    <https://c.gle/ANiao5qez7c1rh5fnKY3MncQ_GKFGLfbm7MIZ-E-1zm7B7sKFT_8CPmuuap7DqoAm774AtV1VxWM85a1jb9AfNblZ1Obtg_RpZP-HDfl7SioAJUIquJtMjITjjQpLq7Iw7cr_bn77ERGLhSDf_Fwq9-ntP_U4cbiRH9p8Ook-kTMGYiOQ8AyGq_57XHS1BkiVgjrdnU2VvopjgU9ujPDZbKjbGos07mCbTpM0QkDYjE3JhZMQ9Gg_1IglKX7ownOseyUQqClyqyOXAypE4k0I8p5X-UUYLv2MtQ8gOdxs-orK4wxAPo>    Build intelligent agents with the Agent Development Kit (ADK).    Today, we published a new course in Google Cloud Skills Boost for    developers ready to start building their own agents with    ADK.<https://c.gle/ANiao5qgY8SI2Em9PbFiHbfv088PKJEUz6B_50HqBWtY_sSyV5FZ0VhNiUrKJrd8hN1lmjTpGkh9O3NOWcreOS9QvNVA2upyBADIWT0YHfDC97SVH_BPaGZSIJeLk2MO8zio7qt6hgrUtjKtOwyg3tFfF_36dfOEGALGXuuS7SupTG9H5xdbf00-nicBNT1YcykrP_d-3o7DJNnq-BNCcnwmz59fhz4aQNF6137FUBQ0Xd2QvN9tsm1u>    It's packed with hands-on labs, core concepts, real-world applications, and    resources from Google Developer Experts (GDEs) and the broader developer    community.    Protect your (BigQuery) data from eager AI agents.    Here‚Äôs a great post with good tips for creating lines of defense around    your BigQuery environment    <https://c.gle/ANiao5obR_2-tdg0wZ4Gq82ZrS9EhM29j5YR4ACgcoFd2F_B6J4NX1W7H0ehdDe1-0mxKgVrUxeNrBu6SZ7jyGrMimdBuzZLOmOawlFr3rQsnZddFCJ8J4de2KKjYn2CxamiDIL-VDxgQOboLT46jgWI-LeQirzGj7CdD8FoaQOmEMPPPtab8e77VzNYgNJkcMK5Ftaoj7WhMEpCqutcmfoeIGjMeDtztgP3jTGxZIgJMQnoru0tsfp9E0Qds8-81UUA96-X-fmxkSDXgiK23e4mAEfpAHbX0MroXRxbC75PPau-dsKAFTtA9b31gHT95-cqvdIy>    to ensure agents don‚Äôt do too much, at too high a cost.    Get smart(er) about Google Cloud networking.    It‚Äôs hard to be good at Cloud without some working knowledge of networking    configurations. This quick reference guide    <https://c.gle/ANiao5otLo0jho4lkekyQOy-2-HeZoCKePTDKWnQ1JGrGS0ExvOY7IwrJ2ic3yAypAmEW-ly8je61PcAF4w0gy2-wxsluJLd1RKd9DiYXj6F8_0LeG8cfVsymLEyBwK8NZLUO14juwow9pBdkWbfBheQ7FBYrtoZBGjwwpDk-B5nJypBcArG9Y8lLyiYIO0izjHWh3ggCfpjJNYPDuOuBhpNmUXk-g8ICtSjVLOZxnliZMjNeV6C56oPMtCNk04HrIWGRk_JJsNHHjXF2n0xTA>    points you to assets that help you learn more.    Set up a GraphRAG setup with Vertex AI and Spanner Graph.    If you‚Äôve got graph data that you‚Äôd like to ground your AI applications    with, you might explore the GraphRAG option. I like this new comprehensive    architecture guide    <https://c.gle/ANiao5rNdUTRPpgDcWLOJhC3z5J7CLavFaxfi2WznzNF-cpL5KxKDt6RMStpV9aA6r4_W39cmaBOFP1m2YJjh9QJNh7ebJvBNrYj7lRR_AF-6uJ8P07TVazE_U2i3jWGrTVTqqsjiU7zpApu_8EimDO5ta8nQmtkneVMzrRX8HQf3lYAtI-mYgjInlb2E8cNorxy19-VfDeWhL514udoaClHZUTYkHbXxA>    that helps you configure this on Google Cloud.    Building production-ready AI Agents?    The Agent Factory video podcast dives deep into design, build, & deployment    on Google Cloud. The podcast covers code, architecture , & practical tips.
